Response Text: I've been to many meetings, taken many surveys, and like other things, we can talk talk talk, but it all comes down to money and what is perceived as the most popular use of funds. Arts are the underdog, so when the city is faced with the question of will it pay to give the Dougherty Arts Center a badly needed new building instead of the rodent-infested, decaying one they have had for decades, or put in a new sports this that or the other at much newer NW rec center, or make deals to get a soccer stadium put in, COA has shown what it values and the citizens follow. ACME must be an advocate that convinces the city that the time to show and prove has arrived. The arts are dying here and we need their support much more than well-sponsored and frequented endeavors, such as sports do.

